<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="170" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,150,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,150,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Biology.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Roberts, H." box="[301,469,150,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" pagination="251 - 272" refId="ref6423" refString="Roberts, H. (1977) Observations on the biology of some tropical rain forest Scolytidae (Coleoptera) from Fiji. II. Subfamily Ipinae - tribe Xyleborini. Journal of Natural History, 11, 251 - 272. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937700770181" type="journal article" year="1977">Roberts (1977)</bibRefCitation>
described the biology of the species, including the gallery system, development, brood sizes, and notes associated species of 
<taxonomicName box="[580,698,186,212]" class="Insecta" family="Scolytinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Scolytinae</taxonomicName>
and Platypodinae, as well as nest parasites (
<taxonomicName authority="Kleine" authorityName="Kleine" authorityYear="1928" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Cyphagogus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fijianus">
<emphasis box="[1204,1436,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Cyphagogus fijianus</emphasis>
Kleine
</taxonomicName>
) (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[252,381,222,248]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[393,507,222,249]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Brentidae</taxonomicName>
). He recorded the species most frequently from 
<taxonomicName box="[1062,1186,222,248]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Meliaceae" genus="Dysoxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1062,1186,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Dysoxylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<taxonomicName box="[1258,1379,222,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Meliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Meliaceae</taxonomicName>
), but also from single host trees in three other families (
<bibRefCitation author="Roberts, H." box="[715,871,258,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" pagination="251 - 272" refId="ref6423" refString="Roberts, H. (1977) Observations on the biology of some tropical rain forest Scolytidae (Coleoptera) from Fiji. II. Subfamily Ipinae - tribe Xyleborini. Journal of Natural History, 11, 251 - 272. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937700770181" type="journal article" year="1977">Roberts 1977</bibRefCitation>
). RAB collected the species only from 
<taxonomicName box="[1312,1436,258,284]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Meliaceae" genus="Dysoxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1312,1436,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Dysoxylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., and it appears to have a strong host preference for this genus. In contrast to 
<taxonomicName box="[1051,1176,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="partitus">
<emphasis box="[1051,1176,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">M. partitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below), the adults emerge around dusk, and are strongly attracted to light (
<bibRefCitation author="Roberts, H." box="[777,933,330,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" pagination="251 - 272" refId="ref6423" refString="Roberts, H. (1977) Observations on the biology of some tropical rain forest Scolytidae (Coleoptera) from Fiji. II. Subfamily Ipinae - tribe Xyleborini. Journal of Natural History, 11, 251 - 272. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937700770181" type="journal article" year="1977">Roberts 1977</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
